title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message:
All power rails present except PP5V_S4RS3 0v AND  PP5V_S0 0v
 Unable to get the datesheet of TPS51980A and pin2 is 0V. It was water damage. Any help please?

title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message: Where was the corrosion?? Resistance to ground on L7520? Corrosion on J6100?

title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message: Resistance to ground on L7520 is 1M and there is no corrosion on J6100. The board came as cleaned no visible corrosion.Thanks.

title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message:
"All power rails present"
Almost all power rails require PP5V_S4RS3 presence; except 3V3 rails...
So you measure something wrong there.

PP5V_S4RS3 comes out from L7520, not from pin2 of U7501!

title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message: My G3H, ppbus_S5, ppdcin_g3h isol, ppdcin g3h, pp3v42_g3h, pp5v_s5 all are ok  and pp5v-s4rs3 is 0v and pp5v_s0 is also 0v ( I checked double ). I am not saying pp5v_s4rs3  comes from U7501 just mention that PIN2 (V5SW) of u7501 is 0 V. THANKS.

title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message:
So you don't have all power rails present.
In fact, apart of 3V3_S5, you are missing all secondary voltages, on big coils...
Post values for PM_SLP_SUS_L, SMC_ADAPTER_EN, PM_BATLOW_L and all PCH's RTC signals.

title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message:
PM_SLP_SUS_L= 3.3v

SMC_ADAPTER_EN=3.3v

PM_BATLOW_L=3.3v

PCH_DSWVRMEN=0v

PM_DSW_PWRGD=3.4v
Thanks.

title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message:
"PCH_DSWVRMEN=0v"
That is bad.

Measure resistance to ground on that line.
Also check R1450 and PPVRTC_G3H...

title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message:
I am so surprised that now  PCH_DSWVRMEN=3.2v
R1450=330k,
PPVRTC_G3H=3.3v
thanks.

title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message:
Solder an wire on SMC_ONOFF_L pad and touch the ground with it.
Check if PM_PWRBTN_L drops to 0V at the same moment.
If yes, PM_SLP_S5_L should rise to 0V too; at least check if is any pulse there...

title: [SOLVED]820-3437-B green light but no Fan spin
message: Did ultrasonic cleaning and now back in normal. Thanks a lot for helping me to solve the problem.
